+\fBlate\fR
+names will be resolved for every event\&. When set to
+\fBnever\fR
+names will never be resolved and all devices will be owned by root\&.
+.RE
+.PP
+\fB\-\-version\fR
+.RS 4
+Print version number\&.
+.RE
+.PP
+\fB\-\-help\fR
+.RS 4
+Print help text\&.
+.RE
+.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
+.PP
+\fIUDEV_LOG=\fR
+.RS 4
+Set the logging priority\&.
+.RE
+.SH "KERNEL COMMAND LINE"
+.PP
+Parameters starting with "rd\&." will be read when
+\fBudevd\fR
+is used in an initrd\&.
+.PP
+\fIudev\&.log\-priority=\fR, \fIrd\&.udev\&.log\-priority=\fR
+.RS 4
+Set the logging priority\&.
+.RE
+.PP
+\fIudev\&.children\-max=\fR, \fIrd\&.udev\&.children\-max=\fR
+.RS 4
+Limit the number of events executed in parallel\&.
+.RE
+.PP
+\fIudev\&.exec\-delay=\fR, \fIrd\&.udev\&.exec\-delay=\fR
+.RS 4
+Delay the execution of RUN intruction by the given number of seconds\&. This option might be useful when debugging system crashes during coldplug caused by loading non\-working kernel modules\&.
+.RE
+.SH "SEE ALSO"
+.PP
+\fBudev\fR(7),
+\fBudevadm\fR(8)
